THE JOB 

Reporting to the Sports Medicine Manager, the Recovery Therapist will be responsible for the following duties: 


To lead and conduct recovery services to scholarship athletes;
To liaise and plan with coaches and other technical support professionals on elite athletes’ recovery process;
To assist in the rehabilitation program;
To plan and implement injury prevention program;
To provide local and overseas on-fields support if required;
To plan and conduct research projects and educational programs for elite athletes and coaches;
To assist training and supervising sub-ordinate; and
To perform any other appropriate duties as assigned by supervisor.

THE REQUIREMENTS 


A university degree or equivalent in recovery therapy, sport therapy or a relevant discipline, preferably a master degree in sports medicine related disciplines;
A minimum of 4 years’ sports relevant working experience;

Experience in managing athletes’ recovery process;

Excellent command of both spoken and written English. Ability to speak Cantonese and Putonghua is a definite advantage; and
Awareness/ knowledge of Child Protection in sport and equal opportunity issues in the context of Hong Kong are an added advantage. 

APPLICATIONS 

Please send the completed Application Form with indication of expected salary to The Human Resources Manager, Hong Kong Sports Institute Ltd, 25 Yuen Wo Road, Sha Tin, New Territories or email: hrdept@ hksi.org.hk . Please quote reference no. JD-202120111-RT in the application

Appointment will be on a fixed term contract. General information is available at the website http://www.hksi.org.hk. 

Applicants who are not invited for interview within six months may consider their applications unsuccessful.

All applications will be treated in the strictest confidence. Personal Data provided by appointees will be used strictly for recruitment and other employment-related purposes only.

THE HKSI IS AN EQUAL OPPORTUNITIES EMPLOYER

Provide innovative and practical designs that accounts for end to end solution of the bank systems. Contribute to address the enterprise architecture target of the bank system transformation projects. Communicate short, medium, long term architecture in a business context to ensure relevant and addressing the business need. Provide architectural direction and guidance to the engineering teams working on the bank transformation project(s). Provide technical oversight, and work with business/product owners, analysts for the design of banking solutions that are consistent with enterprise architectural standards, processes and tools. Ensure solution designs address performance requirements and reusability, scalability, availability/recovery, integrity and security challenges, as well as business functional requirements. Provide expert knowledge of business requirements to the application development and server infrastructure teams, as well as third-party vendors throughout all phases of the development lifecycle. Ensure compliance with all relevant internal policies/standards and external regulatory requirements, including the management of operational/technology risk.
Requirements:
• Degree holder in Computing, Information Technology, Mathematics, Statistics or related disciplines;
• At least 10 years of experience on infrastructure projects, with 3 years in architect role;
• Hands on experience in infrastructure and performing infrastructure architect role;
• Good at networking/server projects;
• Experience of being accountable for significant architectural decisions and provide justification for decisions taken;
• With Banking/Finance background or experience in projects for banking and finance users is preferred;
• Good experience in open platform, network, SAN/NAS/network;
• Good communication skill;
• With qualification of CCNA/CCNP/CCIE/MCSE will be an added advantage;
• Proficient in both spoken and written English and Chinese, fluent in Putonghua is preferable.
(Candidate with less experience will be considered as Information Technology Manager.)

Key Responsibilities:  

Manage content for digital platforms and social media channels to build brand awareness and website management;

Analyze, track and optimize performance of digital marketing campaigns by a range of optimization techniques (e.g. placement, creative testing, audience targeting, re-targeting refinement etc.);
Keep track of competitors’ activities and market trend and assist with the development of digital campaign strategies for the new acquisition and ROI optimization for eah channels;
Provide full spectrum of administrative and marketing supports;
Work closely with advertising and media agencies, internal operations, creative team on marketing initiatives;
Background in digital marketing or social media agency is highly preferable;
Handle ad-hoc projects as assigned.

Requirements: 

Associate degree or above, preferably major in marketing or related disciplines;
Minimum of 3-4 years relevant experience, preferably from beauty industry;
A good team player, strong interpersonal and communication skill;
Creative, presentable and able to work multi-tasks under tight schedules;
Proficient in written and spoken English & Chinese.
Less experience candidate will be considered Marketing Assistant / Marketing officer.

Salary: Negotiable (Depends on qualifications & experience)

You are invited to visit our website at https://www.retens.hk/

We offer 5-day work week and a competitive package to the right candidates. Interested candidates please send your detailed resume, contact telephone numbers, available date, current and expected salary through "Apply Now".  To apply, please contact 3619 8084 or WhatsApp 6740 2856 Human Resources Department. 

Personal data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only.
